This paper deals with the analysis of evolutionary algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of computational intelligence and optimization. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and their runtime, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with the analysis of benchmark functions, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
